## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
We will write a python script `test_app.py` in the workspace to programmatically test all scenarios, verifying:
- Scan endpoint with safe URLs.
- Scan endpoint with malicious URLs.
- Scan endpoint with invalid input format (missing URL, non-string URL, invalid JSON).
- Error handling behavior when the dataset file is deleted/missing.

### Manual Verification
We will run the server using python and send HTTP requests using `Invoke-RestMethod` / `curl` commands to test the endpoints and verify response status codes and body structure.
- Running command: `python app.py` (with standard environment variables)
- API Request tests:
  ```powershell
  # Safe domain check
  Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:5000/scan" -Method Post -Body '{"url": "https://google.com/path"}' -ContentType "application/json"
  
  # Malicious domain check
  Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:5000/scan" -Method Post -Body '{"url": "http://www.malicious-example.com"}' -ContentType "application/json"
  ```
